Cardinal Pell will be remanded in custody on Wednesday to await sentencing.
Waiting for final judgement, we join the Australian bishops in praying for all the victims of abuse,” the statement reads.
Despite promises made by Pope Francis to hold prelates on every level accountable for their part in abuse, Pell has not yet been sanctioned or defrocked.
The gag order in the case frustrated abuse victims and their advocates who were keenly interested in the outcome.
“The fact that Pell was convicted in the first trial is an amazing accomplishment.